The paper discusses the use of delta modeling for software architecture, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of delta modeling for product line development, which falls under the category of software product lines (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the modular modeling of variable software architectures, which is related to software design (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper mentions the consideration of system variability during all phases of development, which is related to software lifecycle management (cs.LO) and the paper also discusses the language-independent approach for modeling system variability, which is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
